profile_positions.description:
Institutional Support to Rwanda’s Green Fund. The Rwanda Fund for Climate Change and Environment (FONERWA) was set up in 2012 to mobilise domestic and international climate finance, and to secure sustainable financing for public and private investment to contribute to environmental sustainability, resilience to climate change, and green growth. 

The consultancy services provide institutional support to FONERWA during the implementation of the Programme, in its management role of the fund, and amongst others, in the areas of general management, institutional and human resource development, monitoring and evaluation, financial project management and reporting.

The following key support areas are covered under the Project:
• Coaching and Mentoring Civil Society Organisations (CSOs) on the relationship between climate change, environment and economic development and development of project proposals targeting FONERWA;
• Building FONERWA’s Institutional Capacity in effective methods of gender inclusion in program design and Implementation;
• Support for the development and roll out of an Environmental and Social Monitoring Framework (ESMF);
• Support in the development and the roll-out of a Resource Mobilisation Strategy to unlock additional funding sources and capacity building for staff to be effective in mobilising a wide range of resources; and
• General management support in the fields of Institutional and Human Resource development, monitoring and evaluation, financial project management and reporting; and development of an ICT strategic plan.
